BanklessDAO was the first DAO I ever joined. I was inspired to become a DAO contributor after hearing the story behind ConstitutionDAO. I was blown away by the fact that an online community can raise 47M in less than a week to acquire a real world asset. Although, they did not succeed in acquiring a copy of the constitution, they sent a powerful message to the world, displaying what DAOs are capable of.

After watching the Constitution DAO event playout, I decided I wanted to become a member of a DAO as well, and help shape the future with like-minded individuals. I first learned what a DAO was from the Bankless Newsletter. I was a big fan of Bankless HQ, the content provided by Bankless helped me become fluid in web3 terminology, and helped me become proficient in utilizing DeFi protocols, and understanding the values of self-sovereignty through blockchain technology. I loved the idea of "breaking up with my  bank," and that blockchain technology allows me to become my own bank, because there is no longer the need for a middleman overseeing my money. I said to myself, "If I'm going to join a DAO, it must be BanklessDAO.

Joining BanklessDAO was the best decision I ever made in my life. The community, and the onboarding experience is amazing! The discord server may be intimidating at first, because there are A LOT of channels, but once you master the BanklessDAO discord server, you can manage any community. I joined BanklessDAO, December 6th, 2021, and the first guild I joined was Research Guild. The guild coordinator was Ernest_Of_Gaia üè¥üÜòüêíüè° ü™ê#4762. He was really cool, and taught me a lot on my very first day. Ernest's internet connection was a little slow that day, and he asked if anyone wanted to volunteer in leading the meeting; there was an awkward silence, so tentatively, I said "yes." Ernest directed me to a Notion of our weekly agenda to read from, and he explained to me that there was a bounty of 1500 BANK for leading the meeting, and he helped me add the BANK token contract to the Polygon network. At this particular time, I have never even added a custom token to metamask; Ernest played an essential role in my web3 experience, as far as utilizing side-chains, becoming a multi-sig signer and becoming a role-holder within the DAO.

Overall, I met some amazing people at BanklessDAO. NF Thinkerüè¥#2814 was the first person to really start doing AMAs at BanklessDAO. I learned about some really interesting projects through his AMAs, and by observing his posts within the discord server. One day he made a post about 'Beanstalk,' the stablecoin based on credit, and I decided to look further into this project. I was super impressed with its 'tokenomics' and decided to write a briefing document on the project, shared it with NF, and expressed interest in co-hosting the AMA with him. The AMA went very well, and we became partners from that day on. Hosting AMAs through the DAOlationships Guild of BanklessDAO, changed my life. Our AMA service allows me to make a full-time living in web3, and I can truly say that I love what I do.

Another key friendship that I made within BanklessDAO was with Humpty Calderon. Humpty is the founder of Crypto Sapiens, a project that spun out of BanklessDAO. I was recruited by 'Sponge' a previous Research Guild role-holder, and he was also the Research Lead at Crypto Sapiens at the time. What I enjoyed most about contributing to Crypto Sapiens early on, was how organized the project was. Humpty is an excellent leader, and through Humpty, I expanded my network fairly quickly. Working with Humpty took my web3 experience to the next level. When Sponge backed down from the project in February 2022, I became the new Research Lead, and Humpty and I started doing weekly discovery calls on Google Meets with some pretty big names in the space. Humpty was very supportive in my journey, and when I earned enough BANK to become an L1, March 7th, 2022, he immediately nominated me to become an L2 Contributor. All of this was in the span of 3 months. BanklessDAO changed my life, and the change was suddenly, right from my very first Research Guild meeting. 

I made countless friends at BanklessDAO, and I met so many amazing people through BanklessDAO. I strongly recommend anyone reading this to join BanklessDAO as well, the experience will change your life.

so,Across does not have these slippage issues ,what you see is what you get.
